@RyuTheRed Unless you have uncorrectable showing up on your router in the downstream channels. if so thats on the ISP. 😂 I know its a lot to take down but this is everything I went through to make sure my internet would work properly

@RyuTheRed see if your router is a 3.0 dosis... if it is see if it has a intel puma 6 chipset in it. if so upgrade to dosis 3.1. turn your IPv4 energy saving mode off. and if all that fails get a active return splitter off of amazon. Literally all these steps taken will fix your internet...

@RyuTheRed yeah make sure all your cables are new (last 5 years) or if there are any cables that aren't being used removed to remove noise. Get new splitters as well. and make sure your internet cable is in the first or most left part of the splitter going into the main line..........
@pattywack6880 Dude I got you on speed dial if I need anything but I think I finally figured it all out 😂
